                    </div>
                    <span>Leadership Skills for Managers(published by McGraw-Hill) provides some unusual slants on the topic of leadership.  For example, the assertion that "leaders form strategic alliances" was something I hadn't considered before.  The Prism of Partnerships showed exactly how to form such alliances.  Thank you for some new slants on an old subject.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Real Asset</div>
